e|[[Christian Bale]]}}\n| {{sort|Cheney|[[Dick Cheney]]}}\n| ''[[Vice (2018 film)|Vice]]''\n|-\n| {{sort|Cooper|[[Bradley Cooper]]}}\n| {{sort|Maine|[[Jackson Maine]]}}\n| ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]''\n|-\n| {{sort|Dafoe|[[Willem Dafoe]]}}\n| {{sort|van Gogh|[[Vincent van Gogh]]}}\n| ''[[At Eternity's Gate (film)|At Eternity's Gate]]''\n|-\n| {{sort|Mortensen|[[Viggo Mortensen]]}}\n| {{sort|Vallelonga|[[Tony Lip|Tony \"Lip\" Vallelonga]]}}\n| ''[[Green Book (film)|Green Book]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=5 style=\"text-align:center\" | [[2019 in film|2019]] <br /><small>[[92nd Academy Awards|(92nd)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" | '''{{sort|Phoenix|[[Joaquin Phoenix]]}} {{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}'''\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" | '''{{sort|Joker|[[Joker (character)|Arthur Fleck / Joker]]}}'''\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" | '''''[[Joker (2019 film)|Joker]]'''''\n| rowspan=5|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/13/movies/oscar-nominations-academy-awards.html|title=Oscar Nominations 2020: 'Joker' and 'Irishman' Lead the Nominees|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|date=2020|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2020-01-13|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sort|Banderas|[[Antonio Banderas]]}}\n| {{sort|Mallo|Salvador Mallo}}\n| ''[[Pain and Glory]]''\n|-\n| {{sort|DiCaprio|[[Leonardo DiCaprio]]}}\n| {{sort|Dalton|Rick Dalton}}\n| ''[[Once Upon a Time in Hollywood]]''\n|-\n| {{sort|Driver|[[Adam Driver]]}}\n| {{sort|Barber|Charlie Barber}}\n| ''[[Marriage Story]]''\n|-\n| {{sort|Pryce|[[Jonathan Pryce]]}}\n| {{sort|Francis|[[Pope Francis|Cardinal Jorge Mario Bergoglio]]}}\n| ''[[The Two Popes]]''\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n==Multiple awards and nominations==\n{{col-begin}}\n\n{{col-break}}\n\nThe following individuals received two or more Best Actor awards:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align: center;\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"55\" align=\"center\" | Wins\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Actor\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"55\" | Nominations\n|-\n| 3\n| Daniel Day-Lewis\n| 6\n|-\n| rowspan=8 | 2\n| Spencer Tracy\n| 9\n|-\n| Jack Nicholson\n| 8\n|-\n| Marlon Brando\n| rowspan=2 | 7\n|-\n| Dustin Hoffman\n|-\n| Gary Cooper\n| rowspan=4 | 5\n|-\n| Tom Hanks\n|-\n| Fredric March\n|-\n| Sean Penn\n|}\n\n{{col-break}}\n\nThe following individuals received four or more Best Actor nominations:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align: center;\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"55\" | Nominations\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Actor\n|-\n| rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\" | 9\n| Laurence Olivier\n|-\n| Spencer Tracy\n|-\n| rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center\" | 8\n| Paul Newman\n|- 3\n| Jack Nicholson\n|- 11\n| Peter O'Toole\n|-\n| rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center\" | 7\n| Marlon Brando\n|-\n| Dustin Hoffman\n|-\n| Jack Lemmon\n|-\n| rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center\" | 6\n| Richard Burton\n|-\n| Daniel Day-Lewis\n|-\n| Denzel Washington\n|-\n| rowspan=10 style=\"text-align:center\" | 5\n| Gary Cooper\n|-\n| Robert De Niro\n|-\n| Leonardo DiCaprio\n|-\n| Tom Hanks\n|-\n| Fredric March\n|-\n| Paul Muni\n|-\n| Al Pacino\n|-\n| Gregory Peck\n|-\n| Sean Penn\n|-\n| James Stewart\n|-\n| rowspan=5 style=\"text-align:center\" | 4\n| Warren Beatty\n|-\n| Charles Boyer\n|-\n| Michael Caine\n|-\n| Albert Finney\n|-\n| Burt Lancaster\n|}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Multiple character nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align: center;\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"55\" | Nominations\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Character\n|-\n| rowspan=14 style=\"text-align:center\" | 2\n| Norman Maine\n|-\n| [[Cyrano de Bergerac]]\n|-\n| [[Vincent van Gogh]]\n|- \n| [[Richard Nixon]]\n|- \n| [[Henry V of England|Henry V]]\n|-\n| [[Abraham Lincoln]]\n|-\n| Eddie Felson\n|-\n| [[Henry VIII]]\n|-\n| 